@page "/"

<PageTitle>Sunfish Anchor</PageTitle>

<div class="anchor-dashboard">
    <header class="anchor-hero">
        <h1>Sunfish Anchor</h1>
        <p class="anchor-hero-sub">
            Local-first desktop dashboard for Sunfish — reports, admin, and audit.
            Your data lives on this device.
        </p>
        <span class="anchor-status-pill" title="Offline-by-default. Sync is opt-in per bundle.">
            Local-first · Offline-by-default
        </span>
    </header>

    <section class="anchor-placeholder">
        <h2>Scope reserved</h2>
        <p>
            This accelerator is scaffolded and positioned as the desktop reports and
            admin dashboard tool. Scope — bundle selection, report catalog,
            authentication model, LocalFirst store wiring — is deliberately deferred
            until the Web Components migration lands (ADR 0017) so Anchor and Bridge
            consume the same component surface from day one.
        </p>
        <p>
            See the <code>README.md</code> in this folder for Anchor's architectural role
            and the deferred-scope checklist.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>

<style>
    .anchor-dashboard { max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif; }
    .anchor-hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
    .anchor-hero-sub { color: #555; margin: 0 0 1rem; line-height: 1.5; }
    .anchor-status-pill { display: inline-block; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 999px; background: #e6f4ea; color: #1e6b3c; font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 500; }
    .anchor-placeholder { margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px dashed #ccc; border-radius: 8px; background: #fafafa; }
    .anchor-placeholder h2 { margin: 0 0 0.75rem; font-size: 1.125rem; }
    .anchor-placeholder p { margin: 0 0 0.75rem; line-height: 1.55; color: #444; }
    .anchor-placeholder code { background: #eee; padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.9em; }
</style>
